The United States expresses deep concern for the civilians affected by the conflict between the Sri Lankan government and the Tamil Tigers. They call on both sides to cease fighting immediately and allow civilians to safely leave the combat zone. The US also urges the Sri Lankan government to stop shelling the "safe zone" and to grant access to international aid groups and media. The US is working with international partners to provide assistance to those who can be reached. They emphasize the importance of both sides adhering to international humanitarian law and express concern about reported violations. The US warns that if the conflict continues, it could further hinder reconciliation and a unified Sri Lanka in the future.